# Example SandboxVars.lua configuration
# This file contains gameplay settings and difficulty options
# It will be auto-generated by the server on first run

# For a complete example, see the Server/wacky_SandboxVars.lua file in this repository
# You can customize game difficulty, zombie settings, survival settings, etc.

# Common settings you might want to customize:

# ZOMBIE SETTINGS
# - Zombie Population: How many zombies spawn (0.0 to 4.0, default 1.0)
# - Zombie Strength: How strong zombies are (1=Sprinters, 2=Fast Shamblers, 3=Shamblers, 4=Slow Shamblers)
# - Zombie Toughness: How much damage zombies can take (1=Tough, 2=Normal, 3=Fragile)
# - Zombie Transmission: How infection spreads (1=Blood+Saliva, 2=Saliva Only, 3=Everyone's Infected)

# LOOT SETTINGS
# - Loot Rarity: How common items are (1=Extremely Rare to 5=Abundant)
# - Food Loot: Amount of food (1=Extremely Rare to 5=Abundant)

# SURVIVAL SETTINGS
# - Temperature: Enable temperature system
# - Rain: Enable rain
# - Erosion: How fast nature takes over (1=None to 100=Fast)
# - Farming Speed: How fast crops grow (1=Very Fast to 5=Very Slow)
# - Hunger Rate: How fast players get hungry (1=Very Fast to 5=Very Slow)

# META EVENTS
# - Helicopter: Enable helicopter event
# - Generator Limit: How long generators work (0-365 days, 0=no limit)

# The server will create this file automatically with default "Apocalypse" settings
# You can modify it after the first server start in the saves/Server/ directory
